title: Masai Mara: African Wildlife Stories
subTitle: The wildlife of the Maasai Mara reveals the raw beauty and realities of one of the most untamed lands, highlighting the daily struggle for survival and the balance between predator and prey.

title: The Lions Rule
subTitle: During the dry season in Ruaha state, a herd of elephants visit the water body at Glade to extract the cleanest water using their trunks.

title: Alpha
subTitle: An eminent religious leader provides a comprehensive insight into the teachings of God, guiding people on the right path.

title: Africa's Hunters
subTitle: Kamuti is a wise old leopard who has reigned over two square miles of prime territory in the Luangwa Valley for ten years, but now she is in trouble. At 13-years-old, Kamuti is one of the oldest leopards in the African bush, and she is not as effective a hunter as she used to be. Kamuti's problems are compounded by her neighbours, the Nsefu pride of lions, who steal her kills and attack her on sight.

title: Epic Animal Encounters
subTitle: A showcase of some of wildlife's most remarkable moments, caught on film by amateurs and professionals. We reveal the full spectrum of animal behaviour: the brutal, the beautiful and the bizarre. Each moment is explained by experts in the field.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: A fragile strip of tropical woodland that extends along the east coast of Australia. It is a place of refuge for fauna, including birds of paradise and cassowaries.

title: The Queen In The North
subTitle: The filmmaker sheds light on a feline predator and her dramatic struggle for survival as she catches prey and feeds her young in the cold and unforgiving conditions.

title: The Americas
subTitle: The Wild West, where coyotes face a snowbound Yellowstone, rattlesnakes emerge in the hundreds, woodpeckers compete to store food, bison battle on the Great Plains, and cranes gather in vast numbers on their age-old migration.

title: Jungle Planet

title: Wild Assassins
subTitle: The filmmaker ventures behind enemy lines to witness how predators in the wild unite in numbers for strength and safety, such as the mighty lion pride and the ferocious wolf pack.

title: Great Parks of Africa
subTitle: The Addo Elephant Park was founded in 1931 and is 1,640km2. It hosts more than 450 elephants and other mammals and was created in response to the elephant population falling as low as eleven.

title: Becoming Prey
subTitle: Mawindo is the Swahili Word for prey. Life in the African Savannah is hard on herbivores but as in the case of predators, they too have their own strategies and skills to survive. However, none of them are prepared for the great hunter.

title: Okavango: River of Dreams
subTitle: Follows the life of lioness Fekeetsa as she travels around her territory in the Upper Okavango river.

title: Zambia Untamed
subTitle: In the Luangwa Valley lies a grove of Ebony trees, home to a troop of baboons. But, there are dangers here as the resident leopard is powerful and agile enough to climb trees.

title: New Kids in the Wild
subTitle: In Central Namibia, a painted wolf pack roams the vast, drought-ravaged wilderness,led by their matriarch, Zeema.

title: Chasing the Rains
subTitle: Anastasia leads her elephant herd north in search of a river, cheetah Kuleta escapes from a pack of hyenas, and wild dog Phoenix has a new baby.

title: Project Tiger
subTitle: The director highlights the incredible comeback of tigers, from a dwindling population due to hunting and poaching to thriving in their wild habitats once more.

title: Extreme Africa
subTitle: South Africa's Drakensberg is one of the continent's most impressive landscapes. It is home to sharp climatic and ecological gradients as physical conditions change for both land-based creatures and the Raptors that swirl in the skies above.

title: White Wolves: Ghosts of the Arctic
subTitle: Ellesmere Island, situated at Canada's northernmost edge, is home to a family of wolves who desperately attempt to raise their pups in the unforgiving environment.

title: The Americas
subTitle: The Atlantic Coast, where wild horses battle, bald eagles chase ospreys and sharks protect fish; raccoons navigate city life, black bears search for food in ancient forests and a 130-year-old oak tree prepares for winter's arrival.

title: The Americas

subTitle: The cloud rainforest is a unique ecosystem that grows in equatorial regions where clouds permanently deposit water, and is home to hummingbird species and snakes.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: There are many fine examples of evolutionary history in the natural world. Animals adapt through a series of small, random mutations and usually do so in order to compete more effectively for food, water and space. Crocodiles are certainly of an ancient lineage, they are believed to be 200 million years old. Sharks have gone through the process of adaptation and evolutionary experimentation as well.
